-- Great-West Lifeco to buy U.S. health administrator
-- 
-- Mon Apr 9, 2007 9:41am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/09/us-greatwestlife-idUSWNA699620070409

 

 TORONTO  (Reuters) - Great-West Lifeco Inc. ( GWO.TO ) said on Monday its U.S. unit will buy an 80-percent stake in Benefit Management Corp., a U.S. third-party health plan administrator. 

 The financial details of the transaction were not disclosed. The deal would add nearly 90,000 medical members to Great-West's healthcare division, the company said. Great-West, one of Canada's largest insurers, said the transaction should be accretive to earnings beginning in 2007 and should close in the second quarter of 2007. The insurer is controlled by Montreal's Power Financial Corp. ( PWF.TO ). Its U.S. unit is Great-West Life & Annuity. Benefit Management's main subsidiary is Montana-based Allegiance Benefit Plan Management, which is the leading medical administrator for large employer groups in Montana. Great-West's shares were up 4 Canadian cents at C$34.70 on the Toronto Stock Exchange in early trading. ($1=$1.15 Canadian)